==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alanine
<hw>Al"a*nine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Aldehyde</ets> + the ending <ets>-ine</ets>. The
<ets>-n-</ets> is a euphonic insertion.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>one of the natural <isa>amino acids</isa> found combined in the
proteins of most living tissues. It can be isolated as a white
crystalline base, <chform>C3H7NO2</chform>. The natural form is the
L-configuration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alantin</ent>⟦br⟧
